{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770831526,"nonce":"MPvTDLbNmcv/F7Br3T9UXr/dqsg=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87qHUp1","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/186","origin":"github"},"title":"worktree_create.sh: layer worktree slug should reflect package repo, not workspace","message":"## Problem\n\n`worktree_create.sh` generates worktree directory names using `issue-{REPO_SLUG}-{ISSUE_NUM}`, where `REPO_SLUG` is auto-detected from the workspace repo's git remote. For both layer and workspace worktrees, this always resolves to `\"workspace\"`, producing paths like:\n\n```\nlayers/worktrees/issue-workspace-48      # layer worktree for core layer\n.workspace-worktrees/issue-workspace-183  # workspace worktree\n```\n\nThis is misleading for layer worktrees -- `issue-workspace-48` looks like a workspace worktree, not a core layer worktree. More importantly, the slug doesn't identify the issue's source repo, so issue numbers from different repos could collide.\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThe slug is always derived from the workspace repo's remote (`ros2_agent_workspace` Ôćĺ `workspace`), regardless of worktree type. For layer worktrees, the issue is typically filed in the package's repo (e.g., `unh_marine_autonomy`), not the workspace repo.\n\n## Proposed Fix\n\nDerive the slug from the issue's source repo:\n\n- **Workspace worktrees**: slug from workspace repo remote (current behavior, correct)\n- **Layer worktrees**: auto-detect slug from the first `--packages` entry's git remote (e.g., `unh_marine_autonomy` has remote `rolker/unh_marine_autonomy.git` Ôćĺ slug `unh_marine_autonomy`)\n- **`--repo-slug` override**: always wins if explicitly provided (for edge cases like a workspace issue requiring layer work)\n\n### Example naming after fix\n\n```\nlayers/worktrees/issue-unh_marine_autonomy-48   # layer worktree, issue in unh_marine_autonomy\n.workspace-worktrees/issue-workspace-183         # workspace worktree, issue in ros2_agent_workspace\n```\n\n## Impact on Other Scripts\n\n- `worktree_enter.sh` and `worktree_remove.sh` use glob patterns to find worktrees (`issue-*-{NUM}`), so they should work with the new naming without changes\n- `worktree_list.sh` displays the directory name, so the improved naming will make its output more informative\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Layer worktree slug is auto-detected from the package's git remote\n- [ ] Workspace worktree slug continues to use the workspace repo remote\n- [ ] `--repo-slug` override still works for both types\n- [ ] Enter, remove, and list scripts work with the new naming\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null}]}